article.headline: North Dakota 49, Northwestern St. 24
article.story: GRAND FORKS, N.D. -- Jake Landry threw for 300 yards and four touchdowns and North Dakota beat Northwestern State 49-24 Saturday night. North Dakota (2-2) was trailing 10-7 until three Landry TDs gave the Fighting Sioux a 28-10 halftime lead over the Demons (1-3). Landry connected with Greg Hardin on three of his TD passes, including a 76-yarder and a 52-yarder. Hardin finished with five catches for 177 yards. Chris Anderson also caught a 71-yard TD pass from Landry. Josh Murray started the third quarter rushing 74 yards for a TD, and added another touchdown on a 60-yard punt return in the fourth. Jake Miller had a 1-yard rushing TD for the Fighting Sioux. Northwestern State's Paul Harris threw for 247 yards and two touchdowns, including a 68-yard TD pass to T.C. Henry. Rumeall Morris threw a 40-yard TD pass to Adrian Reese, and John Shaughnessy kicked a field goal.
